  <Markdown id="intro">
## ActionButton Examples

ActionButton triggers actions on its child components. When clicked, it finds all action blocks (graders, LLMActions, etc.) that are **children** of the button and executes them.

**Key pattern**: Actions must be nested inside ActionButton, not siblings.
  </Markdown>

  <!-- Simple grading example -->
  <Vertical id="grading_example">
    <Markdown id="q1">
### Grading Example

Enter a number and check your answer:
    </Markdown>
    <NumberInput id="num_input" placeholder="Enter 42..." />
    <ActionButton id="check_btn" label="Check Answer">
      <NumericalGrader id="num_grader" target="num_input" answer="42" />
    </ActionButton>
    <Correctness id="num_correct" target="num_grader" />
  </Vertical>

  <!-- LLM feedback example -->
  <Vertical id="feedback_example">
    <Markdown id="q2">
### AI Feedback Example

Write a short paragraph and get AI feedback:
    </Markdown>
    <TextArea id="essay_input" rows="4" placeholder="Write something..." />
    <LLMFeedback id="essay_feedback" />

    <ActionButton id="feedback_btn" label="Get Feedback">
      <LLMAction id="feedback_action" target="essay_feedback">
        Provide brief, constructive feedback on this writing:
        <Ref id="ref_essay" target="essay_input" />
      </LLMAction>
    </ActionButton>
  </Vertical>

  <!-- Multiple actions example -->
  <Vertical id="multi_action_example">
    <Markdown id="q3">
### Multiple Actions

An ActionButton can trigger multiple actions at once:
    </Markdown>
    <TextArea id="multi_essay" rows="3" placeholder="Write something to analyze..." />
    <LLMFeedback id="grammar_feedback" />
    <LLMFeedback id="style_feedback" />

    <ActionButton id="analyze_btn" label="Analyze Writing">
      <LLMAction id="grammar_action" target="grammar_feedback">
        Check this text for grammar issues:
        <Ref id="ref_grammar" target="multi_essay" />
      </LLMAction>
      <LLMAction id="style_action" target="style_feedback">
        Analyze the writing style of this text:
        <Ref id="ref_style" target="multi_essay" />
      </LLMAction>
    </ActionButton>
  </Vertical>

  <Markdown id="note">
### How It Works

When ActionButton is clicked, it uses `inferRelatedNodes` to find actions among its **children** (descendants). This is why actions must be nested inside the button:

```xml
&lt;!-- CORRECT: LLMAction is a child of ActionButton --&gt;
&lt;ActionButton label="Get Feedback"&gt;
  &lt;LLMAction target="feedback"&gt;...&lt;/LLMAction&gt;
&lt;/ActionButton&gt;

&lt;!-- WRONG: LLMAction is a sibling, won't be found --&gt;
&lt;LLMAction target="feedback"&gt;...&lt;/LLMAction&gt;
&lt;ActionButton&gt;Get Feedback&lt;/ActionButton&gt;
```

### Note on CapaProblem

For graded problems, use CapaProblem which provides a Check button automatically. ActionButton is best suited for custom triggers like AI feedback.
  </Markdown>

